name: The Night Before Christmas with Richie Rich

description: Straight from the pages of X-MEN: BLACK SUN comes the mysterious maiden of mysticism, Magik! With her new role in the Marvel Universe solidified, Magik runs into her first true test, an adversary so horrifying, Mephisto himself trembles at the mere whisper of his name! Who is this devilish fiend, what are his terrifying plans for Earth, and how can a lone girl, her Soulsword, and her stepping discs possibly defeat him? It's demon-stomping action as you like it, delivered by the writing team of Dan Abnett and Andy Lanning ( Legion Lost) and penciler Liam McCormack-Sharp ( Medieval Spawn)!
name: The Crossing Guard

description: Magik is forced to make tenuous allies with Dormammu when a new and remarkably powerful new enemy threatens to lay waste to the Splinter Realms.
name: A Gathering of Foes

description: Magik and Nightcrawler unite with the demonic entities known as Dormammu and Mephisto! Will they be able to save Limbo, or will they simply destroy each other instead?
name: The Fall of Hades

description: All the pieces are in place for the final battle between evil and... evil?! Can Magik and Nightcrawler keep Limbo from invading Earth, or will Mephisto, Nightmare and Dormammu rule supreme? It's the chilling conclusion by the writers behind LEGION LOST and the penciler of SPAWN: THE DARK AGES!
name: Bound for Destruction

description: To keep society so "shiny," Ethicorp secretly controls legions of high-tech killers - known on the street as "Triggers"--that act as one-man (or woman) judge, jury and executioner whenever Ethicorp sees something "bad." But be careful, because "bad," like beauty, is often in the eye of the beholder.

The thrill-packed ongoing series continues as Deirdre Myers, a no-nonsense investigative reporter for the daily newsfeed The Relative Truth, looks for answers to a series of mysterious murders and their relation to the shadowy Triggers.
